Package com.robinhowlett.chartparser.charts.pdf

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Aqha
    AQHA track Quarter Horse related information, such as the individual finshing time for the Starter and the AQHA Speed Index figure recorded.
    Breeder
    Stores the name of the Starter's breeder
    Cancellation
    Stores if a race was cancelled and, if provided, for what reason
    Chart
    Utility class for dealing with text and numbers parsed from the chart
    ChartCharacter
    Corresponds to a character within the PDF chart
    ClaimedHorse
    Parses and stores the horse, trainer, and owner name(s) for Starters that were claimed
    ClaimingPrice
    Parses and stores the program number, horse name, and claiming price for each Starter who was available to be claimed
    DeadHeat
    Parses and detects if a dead-heat was declared
    Disqualification
    Parses and stores the Starters who were disqualified and given a new finishing position
    DistanceSurfaceTrackRecord
    Parses the textual description of the race value and converts it into a DistanceSurfaceTrackRecord.RaceDistance instance, including calculating the race value in feet.
    DistanceSurfaceTrackRecord.RaceDistance
    Stores the textual description of the race value, the value expressed in feet, and whether the value is exact or estimated
    DistanceSurfaceTrackRecord.TrackRecord
    Stories the name of the track record holder, the track record time (as both a String and in milliseconds) and the date when the record was set
    Footnotes
    Parses and stores the chart's race notes.
    FractionalTimes
    Parses and stores the textual descriptions of the times recorded by the leader at each fractional point
    Horse
    Stores the horse name and, if available (e.g.
    Jockey
    The rider of the Starter
    Owner
    The owner of the Starter
    PostTimeStartCommentsTimer
    Stores the textual representation of the postTime time, the start comments (which note if any Starter had a poor start), and, where applicable, if the timer used was electronic or not
    Purse
    Parses and stores the value amount, textual description, and any other additional information specific to or enhancing the value
    Purse.PurseEnhancement
    Stores the value Purse.EnhancementType and its textual description
    RaceConditions
    Parses and stores the textual description of the race conditions and, if applicable, the minimum and maximum claiming prices that can be availed of
    RaceConditions.ClaimingPriceRange
    Stores the range of the claiming prices that apply to a claiming race.
    RaceResult
    Represents a single race result on a chart.
    RaceResult.Builder
    Builder pattern used to construct the RaceResult
    RaceResult.Weather  
    RaceTypeNameBlackTypeBreed
    Parses and stores the race type (e.g.
    RunUp
    The registered run-up, measured in feet (the distance between the starting stalls and when the race timer is actually started - a longer run up means the horses are potentially traveling at a much higher speed already versus a short run-up)
    Scratch
    Parses and stores the horse(s) scratched from the race and, if available, for what reason.
    SplitTimes
    Since split times are calculated from the parsed FractionalTimes (with the added benefit of knowing the distance the split applies to), this information is not parsed or stored from the chart
    Starter
    Everything to do with a participant in a RaceResult
    Starter.Builder
    Builder pattern used to create Starter instances
    Starter.Claim  
    TrackRaceDateRaceNumber
    Parses and stores the track name, the race date (as a LocalDate instance) and the race number
    Trainer
    The owner of the Starter
    WeatherTrackCondition
    Parses and stores the textual description of the weather (e.g.
    WindSpeedDirection
    Parses and stores the wind speed (in miles per hour e.g.
    Winner
    The race winner, which provides additional breeding information about the winning horse.
